 MOSES Gama (59) has been sentence to life imprisonment on
Wednesday, 1 March. This follows the brutal murder of his wife, Nurse Nhlebeya. The Chief Albert Luthuli Regional Court Chief heard how the
Mpumalanga man shot and killed the mum of his two kids at her friend's house on
12 March 2019. The victim, who was 42 years old at the time, sustained
multiple gunshot wounds and died on the spot. After the incident, the accused went to Elukwatini Police
Station to hand himself over.  ALSO READ -Â WATCH: ZIYAKHALA - Woman accused of ATM scam moered!  Mpumalanga police spokesman Selvy Mohlala said: "He was then charged for murder and made several court appearances from 13 March 2019 until he was granted bail." He said after he was granted bail, Gama used the opportunity to evade his follow-up court appearances.  You must be SIGNED IN to read comments  "Police were left with the challenging task to locate him. He was circulated in the list of wanted suspects. The investigation team finally managed to track him down in Mofolo North in Soweto in the Gauteng province on 30 December 2022," said Mohlala. He was finally convicted on Wednesday, 22 February and declared unfit to possess a firearm. The acting provincial police commissioner, Major-General Zeph Mkhwanazi, commended the outstanding performance by the team of investigators, the prosecution team, as well as the judiciary. "We welcome the well-deserved sentence that was handed down by the court while emphasising the importance of tightening the grip by all law enforcement agencies in the fight against the pandemic of gender-based violence," he said.    